originalText.text: My daughter has been taking classes at swimjim for about a year and she looks forward to her weekly classes. We can’t say enough about Naomi. The care, patience and attention Naomi shows her students is unmatched. She’s stern but loving and her students truly enjoy swimming with her. I’ve seen Naomi work with children who are afraid of the water and ones like my daughter who have no fear of water- regardless of where the child is in swimming, Naomi will meet them there and work with them. Most importantly she teaches water safety and is super fun. My daughter was recently promoted to another swim group and is now swimming with Raven who we also love. Raven is patient, kind, attentive and truly want her students to be better. We enjoy swimming with SwimJim and happy to have them in our community.

originalText.text: Our son has been going to Swim Jim for some time and we have been so grateful for his instructor Sera. She is so patient and talented. It’s not easy teaching toddlers but she always keeps her cool and brings out the best in them. Our son has gained so much confidence in the water since starting there. 100% recommend!

originalText.text: My 5-year old son has been taking SwimJim lessons with Naomi Distant for a little over a year.  First at the Columbus Avenue location and now at the West End Avenue location.  Thanks to Naomi, my son is confident in the water, loves swimming and his freestyle and backstroke are getting better each day. He even executed a really nice "assisted" dive the other day.  Our son loves Naomi and always looks forward to his swim lesson each week...she is super attentive and has an amazing way with kids that helps them get over any fear, makes them love being in the water and makes them ready to take on any challenges in the water.

originalText.text:
Naomi has been our daughter's regular swim instructor for over 2 years now at this point. Working with her on a consistent basis and really helping to transition our daughter from initially not even feeling comfortable to putting her face in the water blowing bubbles when we she 1st started to being extremely comfortable in the water and really starting to become a solid swimmer.

Naomi has helped our daughter move up in swimming levels in the last handful of months and has a very nice away about her with all of the children while picking up on small nuance differences between each child in the class and what skills each individual child might need more or less assistance with.

She cares quite deeply about each child, having them following the process and believing in that process to help achieve the child's & parents goals collective goals for them. Seeing Naomi's genuine shared excitement with our daughter and myself during various points of the year when our daughter has been able to accomplish certain tasks after practicing them over and over for a number of months-is something that occasionally has even brought a few tears to my eye-with the feeling of deep pride in our daughter's accomplishments after all of her hard work. Naomi shares in this joy with us which is a very special feeling.

As a parent who has attended everyone of my daughters swim classes now for many years on a weekly basis-I truly am able to see her progress and as importantly her comfort level in the water at such a high level. Thank you Naomi for all of your hard work and care in working with our daughter for this extended and consistent period of time. We really appreciate it.

originalText.text: We are very happy with SwimJim! My child is making good progress - has become very comfortable in the water and understands breath control (can jump in going underwater and come back up, can get rings from the bottom of the pool). We really appreciate the calm and encouraging nature of Raven Daniels, our teacher.
